{
  "name": "mac-os-vs--linux-who-s-2-the-mac-observe-34e63d",
  "title": "Mac OS vs. Linux: Who's #2?",
  "description": "The Mac Observer analytical piece reconciling competing claims about #2 desktop OS share between Mac OS X and Linux. Authors aggregate data from HP, IDC, Wired, Gartner, Google browser logs, and analyst commentary \u2014 including Peter Kastner's ~3% Mac share estimate (originally to Wired) as a secondary-source quote. Concludes that definitions matter: Linux installed seats (including piracy, embedded, preloaded non-Windows PCs) and active Mac desktop users are measured inconsistently.",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "created": "2026-04-20",
